  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reintegration Assistance to Returnee Students and Host Communities in Lahj in Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve access to basic (education) services for returnees, host communities and Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in Lahj governorate, an area facing one of the highest return rates in Yemen. By bringing host communities, IDPs and returnees together in cooperation with local government institutions, this initiative will enhance the social cohesion within the community and support the provision of education services and facilities in areas that were identified by the communities and authorities as most in need.  As part of the community stabilization initiative, this project targets four schools in 3 different districts in Lahj Governorate namely: Tuban, Al-Hota and Al-Muasimer districts, in need of rehabilitation, reconstruction, furniture and equipment.</narrative>
  </description>
